title: Coverage Set as NASA’s SpaceX Crew-5 Prepares to Splashdown
summary: NASA will provide coverage of the agency’s SpaceX Crew-5 mission return to Earth from the International Space Station, beginning with undocking coverage live at 12 a.m. EST on Saturday, March 11. The SpaceX Dragon spacecraft is scheduled to undock from the space station at 2:05 a.m., to begin the journey home.

title: Japanese lunar lander company ispace to go public
summary: Japanese lunar exploration company ispace plans to list its shares on the Tokyo Stock Exchange next month, just before the company attempts its first landing on the moon.

title: Relativity Space scrubs first Terran 1 launch attempt
summary: Relativity Space will wait at least three days before making its next attempt to launch its Terran 1 rocket after propellant temperature issues scrubbed its first launch attempt March 8.

title: U.S. intelligence report: China’s commercial space sector to become global competitor by 2030
summary: The fast growth of China’s commercial space industry is helping the country progress toward its goal of edging out the United States in space, the U.S. intelligence community said in a report released March 8.

title: NASA Sets Coverage for Annual Address, Budget Media Call in March
summary: Administrator Bill Nelson will broadcast his annual State of NASA remarks at 3 p.m. EST on Thursday, March 9. The event will air on NASA Television, the NASA app, and the agency’s website.
